			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Good day brother and sisters!<BR>
<BR>
This is just a humble addition to what is already here to inform you of abilities you possess, but may not utilize.<BR>
<BR>
Instill Doubt - This skill IS useful.  It acts as a fear ability, and it has worked on avocets!! (lvl 29 - 30+ monsters)  It can start trains with low lvl mobs, but there is nothing like getting off multiple double attacks on a monster's back ;-)  PS - it even works when you are stunned and feigned, and you can attack and do special attacks while using this skill.<BR>
<BR>
Feign Death - You can bind wounds when feigning on the ground.  Be warned that at about 75% of the time the monster you just feigned might come back to thump you, so be warned.<BR>
<BR>
Sneak - Use sneak! If a merchant won't trade with you, sneak behind it and then trade.  You will soon be a favourite with any party member that needs to buy/sell and can't, not to mention buying supplies for yourself (i.e. bandages, food, etc).<BR>
<BR>
Safe Fall - Another cool monk skill.  I've fallen from Kelethin and the top of Aviak City.  I have even perfected the 'falling corpse trick', a fun crowd pleaser.<BR>
<BR>
Just a word to the wise, two monks can take on yellow or weaker monsters easily with feign death.  One monk tanks, then drops. When the mob attacks the other monk, the monk that just dropped gets up and nails the monster from behind.<BR>
Repeat this until the monster is toasties.  Also, if both monks use instill doubt at the same time...<BR>
<BR>
May the Fist strike hard and never falter!
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
