			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				The Debate on Human or Iksar will never be completely solved. But if you want to decide on which you should play, consider the following: Humans have better faction, and sometimes better armor options (vox bracers etc.) Iksars have a higher natural AC and regen, and better sight. So its a tossup but in my opinion Humans are easier to play. Now as for the last posts, yes monks can solo. More so with a Fungi tunic but they can solo without. I soloed 90% of my time till 46, yes through 30,35,40 and 45 hell levels. It is not hard but it takes alot of time without propor equipment. Best bet is to shell out some cash and get a fungi tunic, then at 35 get 2 Wu's trance sticks, they save alot of time on solos. Lastly in  my opinion, a monks best attribute is Armor class i suggest you get total AC gear, especially past level 40. Take care fellow monks and monk dreamers.<BR>
<BR>
Asche Drache<BR>
50 monk on Xegony
				</font>
