	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Human skills do all max, it's just that monks have a bonus to their dual wield skill seeing<BR>
as it is very important to their way of fighting.  People have told me that the max level is<BR>
(7 * level) +7 I have found this to be incorrect, so that wise guy who made the smart<BR>
comment about holding fire beetle eyes knows where to stick it :)  Although the number is<BR>
very close to that, sometimes hitting it, sometimes 1-3 below it.  According to the formula<BR>
the level 18 max should be 133, mine stopped at 130, so I tried to train it up. It don't<BR>
work; you'll get a message that says you've reached the max of your abilities...Similar<BR>
occurrence at level 17. To the person who said they can only start their monks in Freeport.<BR>
Monks who follow Quellious may only start in Freeport; agnostic monks may only start in<BR>
Qeynos.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
